# PR Automation

## Trigger
Activate when the developer types any of:
- `/pr`
- `/create-pr`
- `Create PR Description`

---

## Step 1 — Analyze the changes

```bash
git diff main --name-only && echo "---STATS---" && git diff main --stat
```

- Categorize: `feat` / `fix` / `refactor` / `chore` / `bump` / `release`
- Detect UI files: anything under `ui/components/`, `ui/pages/`, `ui/hooks/`, `ui/ducks/`, `ui/selectors/`, or matching `*.css`/`*.scss`/`*.tsx`/`*.jsx`

---

## Step 2 — Generate base PR description

Use MetaMask's PR template structure:

**Title** — Conventional Commits format (required for MetaMask PRs):
- `feat(scope):` new feature
- `fix(scope):` bug fix
- `refactor(scope):` restructuring
- `chore(scope):` maintenance

**Description** — Fill the MetaMask PR template:

```markdown
## **Description**

[What changed and why — answer: reason for change + improvement/solution]

[![Open in GitHub Codespaces](https://github.com/codespaces/badge.svg)](https://codespaces.new/MetaMask/metamask-extension/pull/PR?quickstart=1)

## **Changelog**

CHANGELOG entry: [user-facing description in past tense, or "null" if not end-user-facing]

## **Related issues**

Fixes:

## **Manual testing steps**

1. Go to this page...
2.
3.

## **Screenshots/Recordings**

### **Before**

### **After**

## **Pre-merge author checklist**

- [ ] I've followed [MetaMask Contributor Docs](https://github.com/MetaMask/contributor-docs) and [MetaMask Extension Coding Standards](https://github.com/MetaMask/metamask-extension/blob/main/.github/guidelines/CODING_GUIDELINES.md).
- [ ] I've completed the PR template to the best of my ability
- [ ] I've included tests if applicable
- [ ] I've documented my code using [JSDoc](https://jsdoc.app/) format if applicable
- [ ] I've applied the right labels on the PR (see [labeling guidelines](https://github.com/MetaMask/metamask-extension/blob/main/.github/guidelines/LABELING_GUIDELINES.md)). Not required for external contributors.

## **Pre-merge reviewer checklist**

- [ ] I've manually tested the PR (e.g. pull and build branch, run the app, test code being changed).
- [ ] I confirm that this PR addresses all acceptance criteria described in the ticket it closes and includes the necessary testing evidence such as recordings and or screenshots.
```

---

## Step 3 — Ask for optional sections

After showing the base description, ask:

> "Would you like to add any of these optional sections?"
> 1. 🐛 **Related Issue** — which GitHub issue this fixes
> 2. 📝 **Changelog Entry** — confirm/edit the user-facing note
> 3. 🧪 **Manual Testing Steps** — generate QA steps from changes
> 4. 📸 **Screenshots** — capture UI with Playwright (already installed)

Reply: `"none"`, `"all"`, or pick numbers like `"1, 3, 4"`

---

## Step 4 — Handle each optional section

### 🐛 Related Issue
Ask: "What issue number does this fix? (e.g. #1234)"
Insert: `Fixes: #NNNN` under `## **Related issues**`

### 📝 Changelog Entry
Generate a user-facing, past-tense description from the diff.
Ask the developer to confirm or edit.
- End-user-facing: `CHANGELOG entry: Added/Fixed/Updated ...`
- Not end-user-facing: `CHANGELOG entry: null`

### 🧪 Manual Testing Steps
Generate numbered steps based on detected changed files.
Ask the developer to confirm or adjust.

### 📸 Screenshots (uses Playwright — already in the project)

Ask:
1. "What's your dev server URL? (default: `http://localhost:8080` for MetaMask test dapp, or `http://localhost:9011` for storybook)"
2. "Which pages/routes should I screenshot?" (suggest based on changed files — e.g. changed `ui/pages/onboarding-flow/` → suggest onboarding routes)

For EACH route, run:

```bash
mkdir -p .pr-screenshots

# Screenshot via Playwright CLI (already installed as @playwright/test)
npx playwright screenshot <dev-url><route> .pr-screenshots/<route-slug>.png
```

Example for a dashboard route:
```bash
npx playwright screenshot http://localhost:8080/dashboard .pr-screenshots/dashboard.png
```

For capturing a specific state (after interaction):
```bash
# Use Playwright's codegen or write a quick inline script
npx playwright screenshot http://localhost:8080/send .pr-screenshots/send-form.png
```

Reference screenshots in the PR under `## **Screenshots/Recordings**`:
```markdown
### **Before**
<!-- [screenshots/recordings] -->

### **After**
![route description](.pr-screenshots/route-slug.png)
```

---

## Step 5 — Create the PR (optional)

If developer wants to open the PR directly, run:

```bash
# Lint and fix first
yarn lint:changed:fix

# Push branch
git push -u origin HEAD

# Create DRAFT PR (MetaMask requires draft initially)
gh pr create --draft \
  --title "feat(scope): your pr title" \
  --body "$(cat <<'EOF'
[assembled PR description here]
EOF
)"
```

Always open as **draft** — MetaMask policy requires draft until template is filled and CI passes.

---

## MetaMask-Specific Notes

- **Always Conventional Commits** for PR title: `feat(scope):`, `fix(scope):`, etc.
- **Always open as DRAFT** — never "Ready for review" unless explicitly asked
- **UI files** in MetaMask: `ui/components/`, `ui/pages/`, `ui/hooks/`, `ui/ducks/`, `ui/selectors/`
- **Playwright** is already installed (`@playwright/test` v1.55+) — no separate install needed
- **Screenshots folder** `.pr-screenshots/` is gitignored
- **Storybook** runs on port 9011 (`yarn storybook`) — good for component screenshots
- **Test dapp** runs on port 8080 (`yarn dapp`) — good for flow screenshots
